CatDescriptText: Miss Nancy Carroll, dancer, of Pittsburgh, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 14, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that the Federal Government should provide financial aid for students of exceptional ability to further their education when the students are unable to do so for themselves?" answer reads: "Yes, because that will make smarter youths and they will be more useful."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Nancy Carroll wearing patterned jacket and pulled-back hairstyle, holding binder to chest, standing on sidewalk
